Had a few misses too: Was long $ZM stock in Feb, didn't buy calls. Bought a lot of put protection in July, Aug, and they all expired just before the September market drop.  Didn't expect the 2nd/3rd wave in Nov, bought puts on vaccine makers, which were worthless.
K-shaped recovery.  With no travel, dining, upper middle class people will spend money on stuff.  Long $CPRI, $JWN, $TPR, $MOV, $MAT, $HAS calls.
May-Jun: Supply chains will move to Mexico from China.  Housing boom with suburban shift.  Infrastructure spending.  Long $CX, $FCX calls.
May-Jun: A plethora of small businesses going online.  First thing they would do after setting up $SHOP is Advertise. Long $SNAP, $PINS calls.

Mid Mar-Apr:  Fed actions are very aggressive.  Virus will continue to spread, but markets have bottomed.  People will engage in virus-safe activities.  Closed short positions.  Long Outdoor companies - calls on $DKS, $SPWH, $CWH, $VSTO.
Mid Feb: Virus spread can't be stopped because of asymptomatic spread.  Shorted travel and S&P - puts on $H, $NCLH, $RCL, $DAL, $SPY; Long calls on $NFLX, $AMZN
